objkt.name: Balancium #144

metadata.name: Balancium #144
metadata.description:
"Balancium" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022

In the fall of 1931, in Alexander Calder's studio, Marcel Duchamp coined the term 'mobile' for his kinetic sculptures. Later, Calder wrote: "This, in French, means not only 'movable'— but also a 'motive', 'a reason for an act' so I found it a very good word."
 
Around the same year, Bruno Munari started making colorful and whimsical mobiles. He called them "useless machines", existing without any purpose and inviting viewers to just look. Elements are connected with nearly invisible threads or wires, allowing the artist to create the illusion of shapes floating in the air.

Balancium is both a virtual mobile and a useless object. Generated by the code, it undergoes a continual transformation. The movement of the air, or invisible fluid, becomes an integral part of the design and amplifies serenity. 
 
There is a keyboard key that unlocks more variations.

Eko33, is a Swiss-French generative artist who has been at the forefront of digital arts since 1999 when he started writing code to create generative artworks and installations. He made his debut using a Commodore SX-64 and floppy disks. Since then, his work has been exhibited in Museums, International art fairs, and biennales. His work is focused on nonfigurative, generative art while using custom algorithms and innovative technology.

Official Website: https://www.eko33.com/ Official Twitter account: https://twitter.com/eko3316 Official Instagram account: https://www.instagram.com/eko33studio/ https://linktr.ee/eko33 "I create deterministic generative art based on crypto hash seeds. Maximizing algorithmic diversity."

objkt.name: The Televangelist #48

metadata.name: The Televangelist #48
metadata.description:
The Televangelist is a generative audiovisual satire on the crypto technocult.

“GM GM Hear ye 
What a blessed day
Minimum 10 Tez in wallet
To hear the alpha I say

Riches and scams abundant
Where these markets
never sleep
If you’re lucky
You’ll get whitelist
I’m so nice to 
My flock of sheep

Tune in to all my Spaces
And turn notifications on
But if you look away for an instant
Your hope for salvation is gone

Oh you’re so early
By the great gods you’ve been kissed
You’ll make it if you trust in me.”
-Your beloved Televangelist.

Full Project Details here : https://ntent.art/articles/televangelist

SOUND

Generative multimedia sound using Tone.js and a collage of 33 audio clips of IRL televangelists and related journalism.

Desktop : Press S key
Mobile/Small Screens: Click “sound" button
(Make sure mute button on side of your phone is not in "muted" state)

INTERACTIVE

Click above the bottom of the Altar to bring in more non-believers to be converted.

Click below the Altar to flush lost souls out.

Press B to toggle access to the heavens (desktop-only).

GENERATIVE AUDIO

As more non-believers enter, fanaticism & the will to convert increases in the form of increasing bpm.

And the bowing of the devout disciples can be heard if you believe… or turn your volume up high.

RESPONSIVE

Go full-screen and play with the browser size to bounce the non-believers around.

FEATURES

Pay extra special attention to these or you will be whipped. See article above for full info.

objkt.name: Morixels Mans #1040

metadata.name: Morixels Mans #1040
metadata.description:
The Morixels Mans is unique Random Generated 10,000 PFP NFTs, and this collection is for people like me who are nostalgic for pixel arts.
This collection is manually designed.
The original Artwork was designed in 24 by 24 pixels and then resized to 1080 by 1080 resolution. 
The number of Traits in this collection is 12 (120 layers) and it has the ability to make 31,091,558,400 NFTs.
Some ​layers are less than 1 percent of the total, some 100 percent, and some between 0.1 and 100 percent.
To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.
To Produce this collection, all the layers were designed pixel by pixel, which was time-consuming and difficult. And this greatly increases the value of this collection.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

Twitter: @Morixels

Website: https://morixels.com/

Designed by: @morteza_yousefy
Made in 2022
